<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>We need MORE PVP servers!!!If Rallos Zek ever goes down, we are screwed.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Farleytron">Farleytron</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:38 a.m. 23/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> We need MORE PVP servers!!!If Rallos Zek ever goes down, we are screwed.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Being an evil character myself, I have had the guilty pleasure of attacking other players out of whim, and of looting previously "murdered" characters by other players. But it is absolutely integral to a realistic role-playing environment to:

<BR>A) Attack another player and kill him if the need suit you, or your unruly mob.
<BR>B) Defend yourself against a slanderous piece of scum who insults your mother in a bar.
<BR>It seems almost ludicrous that the game designers came up with such sorrow excuses for PK-er fixes.I see PVP players on other non-PVP servers once in a great while, but what good is that if no-one else is on level playing field.
<BR>This has nothing to do with the title post, but if we lose Rallos Zek to a major disaster such as a hardware failure, what the fuck are we supposed to do then. I hate the other servers and the gay ass people that play there. Like the nerds whose parent drove them to school so they wouldnt get there asses kicked. Life is fear, and RPG's are supposed to emulate that fear on the computer.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
